post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text: Vista Virtual Field Day was a blast! This year with not being able to play together, students were challenged to participate in fun games at home including towel flip, paper airplane corn hole, backboard bank-it, and tennis shoe tower. post_text:
Vista students, sponsored by the National Junior Honor Society (NJHS), will be taking part in The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society’s (LLS) Pasta for Pennies, presented by Olive Garden. During the program, students collect money to support LLS’s mission to find cures and ensure access to treatments for blood cancer patients.

Pasta for Pennies will begin on Monday, March 2nd, and will end on Friday, March 13th. Students in Young 5’s-5th grade will receive individual penny boxes for collecting spare change. There will also be a large donation box in each homeroom for all grade levels. Students can also collect donations online: https://events.lls.org/pages/mi/VistaCharterAcademy-2020

The class that collects the most money will win an Olive Garden lunch party. Thank you in advance for your help!

The cost to participate is $1.00 for all Y5’s-8th grade students and staff . The NJHS students will collect donations on Monday, November 11th, and Tuesday, November 12th. If you do not donate, you cannot participate.

Proceeds from Dollar Decades Day will benefit the Family Network of Wyoming. Our donation will help with their food bank and positively impact families in our community! If you would like to more information about the Family Network of Wyoming, please visit their website at https://fntw.org/.

post_text: Vista will be participating in ColorCycle this year! ColorCycle is a program where we collect used and dried out markers and send them back to Crayola to be recycled. If you have any markers that no longer work, please send them to school with your child and they can be given to Mrs. Blair for this recycling program. They can be any brand, not just Crayola. If you would like more information about this program, please visit the following website: https://www.crayola.com/colorcycle.aspx

post_text: On Friday Young Fives celebrated Fall with a Camping/Bear Hunt Party! They learned facts about bears while enjoying their new books and s'mores around the campfire. They all had a camping hotdog lunch, made caves for their stuffed animals and went on a bear hunt. They even found a giant bear inside the cave in their classroom!

post_text: The 5th grade students enjoyed a field trip to Heidi's Farm Market where they explored their way through a corn maze. They searched for five different checkpoints where they learned fun facts about the Apollo 11 Space Mission. After the maze, they enjoyed having some apple cider and donuts. Great time even though it was soggy!
